Title: CP in Orbifold Models
Authors: T.Kobayashi and C.S.Lim
Comments: 11 pages, KOBE-TH-94-06, Kanazawa-94-20, Latex file
Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B343 (1995) 122-127
\\
  We study CP in orbifold models. It is found that the orbifolds always have
some automorphisms as CP symmetry. The symmetries are restricted non-trivially
due to geometrical structure of the orbifolds. Explicit analysis on Yukawa
couplings also shows that CP is not violated in orbifold models.
